      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Linear elastic constitutive model with frictional contact (mu=0.2) at screw-rod and rod-plate interfaces; justified by sub-yield loading regime for stiffness QoI and sensitivity analysis confirming <5% QoI sensitivity to friction coefficient in range 0.1–0.3.",
      "rationale": "The ASTM F1717 compression-bending test operates primarily in the elastic regime for stiffness and yield force QoIs. Linear elastic material models with isotropic hardening for post-yield behavior are appropriate. Frictional contact at metal interfaces is represented with Coulomb friction; sensitivity analysis over mu=0.1 to 0.3 shows <3% variation in stiffness QoI, confirming model form adequacy."
    },
