      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions replicate ASTM F1717 protocol across at least two load rates and two laboratories; environmental conditions (temperature, humidity) documented.",
      "rationale": "Testing was performed at a single displacement rate (5 mm/min) per ASTM F1717 at two independent laboratories. While dual-laboratory testing increases confidence, only one test condition (load rate) was evaluated. Rate sensitivity was not characterized experimentally, representing a gap. This factor is below required level 3; the gap is acknowledged and accepted given the quasi-static loading regime and prior literature supporting rate-insensitive response for Ti-6Al-4V at these strain rates."
    },
